Body:
Description: Need assistance with migrating Enterprise Auditor 11.6 to new set of Windows servers 2022.
- recap, we are getting cert errors on jobs using the file system proxy (which is dedicated to scanning for sensitive data on Netapp.  
- Working with support enigneer Ian Ranstrom, we don't know if the errors are related to either the in-place OS upgrade or upgrading from StealthAudit 11.5 to NEA 11.6
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Frantz Baptiste, Bradley Dickinson

We installed the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor on the new server.

We migrate the data from the old server to the new server.

We installed the proxy and the Sensitive Data Add-on in the new proxy server.

Now, we are waiting for your DBA to run the SQL script to change the server's name in the database before we can launch the Enterprise Auditor application.

Â 

Next meeting:

We will launch the application

Update the host list with the new proxy server

Install the AIC

The customer will recreate the schedule for jobs that were scheduled to run.

Next Steps Updated: We will launch the application
Update the host list with the new proxy server
Install the AIC
The customer will recreate the schedule for jobs that were scheduled to run.
What We've Learned Updated: Due to some issues caused by the in-place OS upgrade, the customer has to migrate from the old 2022 server to a new 2022 build server.

Next Steps Updated: We will install NAM
We will review the migration overall

Next Steps Updated: I will verify that the service account can communicate with the new proxy.
I will drop the data and rescan the file system.

I will review this ticket with the customer tomorrow and close it.
